17	de	Erstberatung	erstberatung	<h2>Erstberatung:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Das erste Beratungsgespr&auml;ch </strong>vor der IVF-Behandlung findet in unserer IVF-Klinik oder als VideoCall vor Ihrer Ankunft in Istanbul statt. Der Arzt bespricht mit Ihnen den Startpunkt der Behandlung, die Stimulation und den weiteren Ablauf.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Das Erstgespr&auml;ch ist ein pers&ouml;nliches Gespr&auml;ch, das entweder in unserer Klinik oder alternativ telefonisch/&uuml;ber Zoom stattfindet.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Bei diesem Termin treffen Sie Ihren Fruchtbarkeitsspezialisten, </strong>der Ihnen Ihre Testergebnisse erkl&auml;rt, Ihre Krankengeschichte (vorherige Schwangerschaften, Fehlgeburten, Geburten oder Behandlungen, falls vorhanden) bespricht, alle Ihre Fragen beantwortet und Ihren pers&ouml;nlichen Behandlungsplan bespricht.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Das Gespr&auml;ch konzentriert sich auf das, </strong>was f&uuml;r Sie am relevantesten ist. Es ist oft eine gute Idee, wenn Sie vor dem Erstgespr&auml;ch eine Liste mit Fragen vorbereiten, aber Sie k&ouml;nnen uns auch gerne im Nachhinein mit Fragen kontaktieren.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Bitte bereiten Sie uns Ihr</strong> AMH-Testergebnis, Ihr TSH-Testergebnis, einen schriftlichen HSG-Bericht (Hysterosalpingographie) und einen Spermienanalysebericht Ihres Partners vor, wenn Sie eine IVF-Behandlung w&uuml;nschen oder von uns beurteilen lassen m&ouml;chten, welche Behandlung f&uuml;r Sie am besten geeignet ist.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Der pers&ouml;nliche Teil des Termins umfasst </strong>eine erweiterte Beckenuntersuchung, die uns hilft, Ihre Eizellenreserve, den Gesundheitszustand Ihrer Geb&auml;rmutter, Ihres Endometriums (Geb&auml;rmutterschleimhaut), Ihrer Eierst&ouml;cke und Follikel zu beurteilen.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Wenn Sie bereit sind, </strong>k&ouml;nnen Sie mit der Behandlung beginnen, sobald Ihr n&auml;chster Menstruationszyklus beginnt.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Wir organisieren die Lieferung Ihrer Fruchtbarkeitsmedikamente und Sie nehmen an einer Schulung teil, in der die Dosierung und der Einnahmezeitpunkt Ihrer Medikamente behandelt werden.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img src="/media/uploads/2024/07/22/image-20240722121752-1.png" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\nN&auml;chster Schritt: <u><a href="https://drsagiroglu.com/de/schritt-fur-schritt-ivf?item=Stimulating-your-ovaries"><span style="color:#e72254">3. Stimulieren</span></a></u><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="/media/uploads/2024/07/22/image-20240722121752-1.png" /></h3>	2	Das erste Beratungsgesprch vor der IVF-Behandlung findet voreinander oder als VideoCall vor Ihrer Ankunft in Istanbul statt.
3	en	Stimulating	Stimulating-your-ovaries	<h2>Stimulating your ovaries:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>To maximize the number of eggs we collect, </strong>you will start daily injections of stimulating hormone over a period of 10-12 days. During this time, we&rsquo;ll monitor your response with blood tests and ultrasound scans and optimize your medication doses..</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>A few days after your period starts (either following medication or normal start without medication)</strong>, you will go to your fertility clinic for a baseline vaginal ultrasound. This ensures that you don&rsquo;t have any cysts in your ovaries, the lining of your uterus is thin, and confirm that your ovaries are in a resting state so that you can start stimulation medication.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>This involves taking injections that are synthetic or purified forms of FSH and LH (also called gonadotropins),</strong> which are more potent than what your body makes naturally. You will take these injections subcutaneously every day. The injections are given just below your skin, have minimal discomfort, and feel like a sharp pinch. As you take your injections, multiple follicles will grow and will make more and more reproductive hormones (mainly estrogen and a small amount of progesterone).</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Next,</strong> you will take another subcutaneous injection called either GNRH agonist or GNRH antagonist. As your follicles continue to grow and produce more and more estrogen, the brain signals your ovaries to release eggs prematurely before they are retrieved. This injection prevents your brain from telling your ovaries to release eggs before we can collect your eggs during the egg retrieval procedure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Over the next 8-12 days,</strong> you will take your injections and come into the clinic for 3-5 short visits (usually 15-20 minutes each) to have ultrasound examination. During the monitoring visits, we will measure both the thickness of the lining of your uterus and the size of your follicles. In response to the increasing levels of hormones, your follicles will become progressively larger, and the lining of the uterus will become thicker. We may adjust your hormone injection dose based upon the results of each monitoring visit. After each visit, we will review any adjustments in your medication dose and schedule the next visit.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>We will monitor your follicle sizes closely until the largest follicles (also called lead follicles) reach an average size of 18-22 mm.</strong> At this point, we will determine the best timing for you to take your final medication (the &ldquo;trigger shot&rdquo;) to help the eggs in the follicles reach maturity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Once stimulation has been completed and follicles have reached their optimal sizes, </strong>it is time to proceed with an injection (subcutaneous, intramuscular, or both) to trigger ovulation. This medication causes eggs in the follicles to mature, thereby initiating the ovulation process. Many women will ovulate and release eggs from their follicles 37 to 38 hours following the trigger injection.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img src="/media/uploads/2024/07/22/image-20240722121752-1.png" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em>Next step:<span style="color:#e72254"> </span><u><a href="https://drsagiroglu.com/en/journey/?item=collecting-your-eggs-and-sperm-sample"><span style="color:#e72254">4</span></a></u><a href="https://drsagiroglu.com/en/journey/?item=collecting-your-eggs-and-sperm-sample"><span style="color:#e72254"><u>. Collecting</u></span></a></em><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="/media/uploads/2024/07/22/image-20240722121752-1.png" /></h3>	3	To maximize the number of eggs we collect, you will start daily injections of stimulating hormone over a period of 10-12 days.
4	en	Collecting	collecting-your-eggs-and-sperm-sample	<h2>Collecting your eggs and sperm sample:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>We will collect your eggs using a minor procedure typically lasting less than 30 minutes</strong> and you&rsquo;ll be given a mild intravenous sedation, so you don&rsquo;t feel any pain. On the same morning your male partner will produce a semen sample..</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The time of your egg retrieval is dependent on the time of your trigger shot.</strong> For instance, if the trigger shot(s) are administered at 10 pm on Monday evening, the egg retrieval will take place at 10 am on Wednesday morning. The type and number of trigger shots required is dependent on the specifics of your personalized treatment plan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Upon your arrival for the egg retrieval procedure,</strong> your care team will accompany you to the surgical center at your fertility clinic. Once there, your nurse will take routine vital signs before initiating an intravenous (IV) drip. You will then meet with the fertility physician to review the details of the egg retrieval process.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>You will also meet with the anesthesiologist,</strong> who will explain the sedation to be used for the egg retrieval. Once you are ready for the procedure, your nurse will escort you to the surgical suite, where your team will help you lay flat on the procedure table. A mask will be placed on your face to provide oxygen to assist your breathing, and you will undergo sedation. While under sedation, you will be breathing on your own. &nbsp; Anesthesia will prevent you from feeling or remembering the procedure and will be administered through your intravenous (IV) line.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Once you have fallen asleep under sedation,</strong> your physician and care team will proceed to carefully place your legs in stirrups. Prior to the procedure, your physician will clean the pelvic area and vagina to minimize the risk of infection. The ultrasound probe will be inserted into the vagina to confirm the location of the ovaries and their follicles, as well as the bladder, intestines and major blood vessels.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Subsequently, a small gauge will be guided through a channel at the end of the ultrasound probe.</strong> The needle will be guided through the vagina and into each individual follicle in each ovary using ultrasound technology. The fluid will be aspirated (extracted) from each follicle with suction and examined under a microscope by the embryology laboratory staff to confirm the presence of an egg.<br />\r\nOnce all follicles have been aspirated, your physician will conduct an ultrasound to verify that there is no abnormal bleeding. The entire procedure is typically completed within 20 minutes or less.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Following the egg retrieval procedure,</strong> you will be transferred to the post-anesthesia care unit (PACU) or recovery room, where our nursing staff will be on hand to provide care and support.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Once you are fully awake,</strong> your physician will discuss with you the results of the egg retrieval and the number of eggs obtained. During recovery, your nurse will closely monitor your oxygen levels, blood pressure, heart rate, and pain level.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img src="/media/uploads/2024/07/22/image-20240722121752-1.png" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em>Next step:</em> <em><u><a href="https://drsagiroglu.com/en/journey/?item=retrieval-collection"><span style="color:#e72254">5. Fertilizing</span></a></u></em><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="/media/uploads/2024/07/22/image-20240722121752-1.png" /></h3>	4	We will collect your eggs using a minor procedure typically lasting less than 30 minutes and youll be given a mild intravenous sedation, so you dont feel any pain.
5	en	Fertilizing	retrieval-collection	<h2>Fertilizing your eggs and growing embryos:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The embryology team will utilize a highly specialized glass needle to inject a single normal sperm into each mature egg under the guidance of a state-of-the-art microscope.</strong> The embryos will then be monitored continuously for 5 to 6 days..</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Once the eggs have been collected,</strong> they are combined with sperm in the IVF laboratory within a period of 2-4 hours following the egg retrieval. If you have a male partner, sperm will be produced by him through masturbation.<br />\r\nThe ICSI method is the standard procedure to facilitate fertilization, as it has been proven to dramatically increase the success rate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>ICSI is a process whereby a glass pipette, </strong>which is finer than a human hair, is used to collect a single sperm and inject it into the cytoplasm of the egg cell. The ICSI method is performed with the assistance of a specialized microscope, which is equipped with a range of enlargement lenses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Approximately 18-24 hours after the egg and sperm come together, </strong>the genetic material of both the female and male combine to form the zygote (fertilized egg) and fertilization is confirmed the morning after your egg retrieval. On average, approximately 70-90% of mature eggs are fertilized during IVF.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Following the egg retrieval and IVF procedure,</strong> your team will contact you to provide an update on the number of fertilized eggs that have developed into zygotes. In an incubator (a device used in IVF laboratories that simulates the temperature, oxygen, carbon dioxide, and nutrient levels in the fallopian tubes and uterus) the zygote will undergo daily growth and development, as if it were in a natural environment. The cells of the zygote divide daily..</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Five Days&nbsp;after the egg retrieval,</strong> the embryo(s) have grown significantly and has divided (grown) to a collection of hundreds of cells and becomes the most advanced stage embryo called a blastocyst. On day 5 after egg retrieval and fertilization, the embryo can be transferred into your uterus (fresh embryo transfer) or, they may undergo genetic testing (preimplantation genetic testing, PGT) and freezing for future transfer.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img src="/media/uploads/2024/07/22/image-20240722121752-1.png" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em>Next step: <a href="https://drsagiroglu.com/en/journey/?item=embryotransfer"><span style="color:#e72254"><u>6. Embryo Transfer</u></span></a></em><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="/media/uploads/2024/07/22/image-20240722121752-1.png" /></h3>	5	The embryology team will utilize a highly specialized glass needle to inject a single normal sperm into each mature egg under the guidance of a state-of-the-art microscope.
2	en	Initial Consultation	initial-consultation	<h2>Initial Consultation:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The first consultation</strong> before IVF treatment takes place in our IVF Clinic or as a VideoCall before your arrival in Istanbul. The doctor will discuss with you the starting point of the treatment, the stimulation, and the course of action..</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The initial interview is a personal conversation that either takes place at our Clinic or alternatively over the phone / via Zoom.&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>During this appointment,</strong> you will meet with your fertility specialist who will explain your test results, discuss your medical history (previous pregnancies, miscarriages, births or treatments, if any), answer any questions you may have and discuss your personalized treatment plan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The interview takes offset in what is most relevant for you to focus on.</strong> It is often a good idea for you to prepare a list of questions before the initial interview, but you are also welcome to contact us with questions afterwards.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Please provide us with your AMH-test result, </strong>your TSH-test result, written report of HSG&nbsp;(hysterosalpingography) and semen analyze report of your partner if you want to do IVF treatment or need us to assess which treatment would be best for you.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Face to face part of the appointment includes </strong>an advanced Pelvic Assessment Scan which will help us assess your egg reserve, the health of your uterus, endometrium (lining of the womb), ovaries and follicles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>If you are ready to go ahead,</strong> you can start treatment as soon as your next menstrual cycle begins.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We will arrange for the delivery of your fertility medications, and you will attend a training session, which will cover dosing and timing of your medications.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img src="/media/uploads/2024/07/22/image-20240722121752-1.png" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em>Next step: <u><a href="https://drsagiroglu.com/en/journey/?item=Stimulating-your-ovaries"><span style="color:#e72254">3. Stimulating</span></a></u></em><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="/media/uploads/2024/07/22/image-20240722121752-1.png" /></h3>	2	The first consultation before IVF treatment takes place face to face or as a VideoCall before your arrival in Istanbul.
1	en	Preparation	treatment-preparation	<h2>Treatment Preparation:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>It is advisable to have some essential tests carried out before travelling to Istanbul to commence your treatment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>HSG&nbsp;(Hysterosalpingography)</strong> Is an X-ray procedure that is used to view the inside of the&nbsp;uterus&nbsp;and&nbsp;fallopian tubes. It often is used to see if the fallopian tubes are partly or fully blocked. It also can show the inside of the uterus is in normal size and shape and existence of any&nbsp;polyps or fibroids&nbsp;that may need treatment before we can start your IVF treatment.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>AMH&nbsp;(Anti M&uuml;llerian Hormone)</strong> The level of AMH in a woman&#39;s blood is generally a good indicator of her ovarian reserve and shows which treatment option is best for you and which hormone dosage is appropriate during the treatment. AMH does not change during your menstrual cycle, so the blood sample can be taken at any time of the month even while you are using oral contraception.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>TSH&nbsp;(Thyroid Stimulating Hormone)</strong> The result indicates whether your metabolism is balanced; if not, the pituitary gland might release more prolactin, which can affect egg quality and fetal growth during pregnancy.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Semen&nbsp;analysis: </strong>Is a test of a man&rsquo;s&nbsp;sperm&nbsp;and semen. Also known as a sperm count or&nbsp;male fertility&nbsp;test, its results show how many sperm are released, as well as how they&#39;re shaped and how well they move.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img src="/media/uploads/2024/07/22/image-20240722121752-1.png" style="height:39px; width:1230px" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em>Next step: <a href="https://drsagiroglu.com/en/journey/?item=initial-consultation"><u><span style="color:#e72254">2. Initial Consultation</span></u></a></em><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="/media/uploads/2024/07/22/image-20240722121752-1.png" style="height:39px; width:1230px" /></h3>	1	It is advisable to have some essential tests carried out before travelling to Istanbul to commence your treatment.
7	en	Embryo Transfer	embryo-transfer	<h2>Embryo Transfer:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Regardless of whether you have a fresh or frozen embryo transfer, </strong>you and your partner (if applicable) will be brought into the treatment room for your embryo transfer. The embryologist will verify your identity and confirm the number and identity of the selected embryos.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The ultrasound transmits sound waves,</strong> so a full bladder allows for clear imaging of the uterus. &nbsp;To ensure an optimal bladder filling for the transfer, we kindly request you to drink 1 to 1,5 liters of water prior to your scheduled appointment. &nbsp; This allows your physician to place your embryo(s) at the most optimal location within the uterine lining.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Please note that you will either wear a gown or remove your trousers and underwear for the procedure.</strong> The next step is for you to be assisted onto the examination table and to lie on your back. An ultrasound probe will be placed on your lower abdomen to confirm the location of the uterus and ascertain if the uterine lining can be seen easily.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The physician will insert a speculum into the vagina and identify the cervix. </strong>Any excess mucus or discharge will be removed, and the physician will proceed with the next step.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Once the embryo(s) has been selected by the embryologist,</strong> it will be loaded into a special embryo transfer catheter containing a small amount of fluid and air.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The physician will then place the embryo catheter through the cervical external opening using ultrasound guidance. </strong>Subsequently, the catheter&#39;s tip will be placed in the uterine cavity at a depth of approximately one to 1-1,5 centimeters from the uterine fundus..</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Using the attached syringe, </strong>your physician will push the syringe handle and the embryo(s) will then be transferred from the catheter tip into the lining of the uterus. Once the transfer has been completed and the embryo(s) are confirmed to be in the uterine cavity, first the catheter then the speculum will be slowly removed, and the procedure will be concluded.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Once the embryo transfer has been completed, </strong>you will be asked to rest in the transfer room for 10 minutes. Once the procedure is complete, you will be able to dress, empty your bladder, and leave the facility. There is no sedation or pain medication required for this procedure.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img src="/media/uploads/2024/07/22/image-20240722121752-1.png" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em>Back to first step: </em><em><u><a href="https://drsagiroglu.com/en/journey/?item=vorbereitung"><span style="color:#e72254">1.&nbsp;Preparation</span></a></u></em><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="/media/uploads/2024/07/22/image-20240722121752-1.png" /></h3>	7	Regardless of whether you have a fresh or frozen embryo transfer, you and your partner (if applicable) will be brought into the treatment room for your embryo transfer.
12	tr	Yumurtalklarn Uyarlmas	yumurtalarin-uyarilmasi	<h2>Yumurtalklarn Uyarlma S&uuml;reci:</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Toplayacamz yumurta saysn arttrmak amacyla, </strong>10-12 g&uuml;n s&uuml;recek yumurtalklarnz uyarc ila&ccedil; enjeksiyonlarna balayacaksnz. Bu d&ouml;nemde kan testleri ve ultrason taramalaryla yumurtalklarnzn tepkisini izleyecek ve ila&ccedil; dozunu ayarlayacaz.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&Acirc;det kanamanz baladktan (adet s&ouml;kt&uuml;r&uuml;c&uuml; ila&ccedil;la veya kendiliinden) birka&ccedil; g&uuml;n sonra </strong>vajinal ultrason muayenesi i&ccedil;in geleceksiniz. Bu ultrason yumurtalklarnzda kist olmadn, rahim duvarnn ince olduunu ve yumurtalklarnzn uyarc ila&ccedil;lara balamak i&ccedil;in uygun olduunu netletirmek i&ccedil;in yaplr.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Bu s&uuml;re&ccedil;te, v&uuml;cudunuzun doal olarak &uuml;rettiinden daha etkili FSH ve LH&#39;nin (gonadotropinler olarak da adlandrlr) sentetik veya saflatrlm t&uuml;rleri olan ineleri kullanacaksnz. </strong>Bu ineleri her g&uuml;n cilt altna yapacaksnz. Enjeksiyonlar deri altna yaplr, keskin bir &ccedil;imdik hissine benzeyen &ccedil;ok az rahatszlk verir. Enjeksiyonlarnz yaptk&ccedil;a, fazla sayda folik&uuml;l b&uuml;y&uuml;yecek ve daha fazla &uuml;reme hormonu (esas olarak &ouml;strojen ve az miktarda progesteron) &uuml;retilecektir.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Daha sonra, GNRH agonisti veya GNRH antagonisti ad verilen baka bir cilt alt inesi yapmaya balayacaksnz. </strong>Folik&uuml;lleriniz b&uuml;y&uuml;meye ve daha fazla &ouml;strojen &uuml;retmeye devam ettik&ccedil;e, beyniniz yumurtalklarnza yumurtalarnz brakmalar i&ccedil;in sinyal g&ouml;nderir. Bu ineler, biz toplamadan &ouml;nce yumurtalarnzn erkenden braklmalarn engeller.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sonraki 8-12 g&uuml;n boyunca</strong> inelerinizi yapacak ve ultrason muayenesi i&ccedil;in 3-5 defa kontrole geleceksiniz. Kontrol ziyaretleri srasnda hem rahim duvarnzn kalnln hem de folik&uuml;llerinizin boyutlarn &ouml;l&ccedil;eceiz. Artan hormon seviyelerine yant olarak, folik&uuml;lleriniz giderek b&uuml;y&uuml;yecek ve rahim i&ccedil; tabakas kalnlaacaktr.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Her kontrolden sonra ila&ccedil; dozunuzu g&ouml;zden ge&ccedil;irecek ve bir sonraki ziyaretinizi planlayacaz.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>En b&uuml;y&uuml;k folik&uuml;ller (&ouml;nc&uuml; folik&uuml;ller olarak da adlandrlr) ortalama 18-22 mm boyutuna ulaana kadar folik&uuml;l boyutlarn yakndan takip edeceiz.</strong> te bu aamada, folik&uuml;llerdeki yumurtalarn olgunlamasna y&ouml;nelik son inenizi (&ldquo;tetikleyici ine&rdquo;) yapmanz i&ccedil;in en uygun zamanlamay belirleyeceiz.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Uyarm tamamlandktan ve folik&uuml;ller ideal boyutlarna ulatktan sonra, </strong>yumurtlamay tetikleyecek bir inenin (deri alt ya da kas i&ccedil;i) yaplmasnn zaman gelmitir. Bu ila&ccedil; folik&uuml;llerdeki yumurtalarn olgunlamasn salayarak yumurtlama s&uuml;recini balatr..</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img src="/media/uploads/2024/07/22/image-20240722121752-1.png" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em>Sradaki Adm: </em><em><u><a href="https://drsagiroglu.com/tr/adim-adim-tup-bebek?item=collecting-your-eggs-and-sperm-sample"><span style="color:#e72254">4. Y</span></a></u></em><a href="https://drsagiroglu.com/tr/adim-adim-tup-bebek?item=collecting-your-eggs-and-sperm-sample"><em><u><span style="color:#e72254">umurta Toplama</span></u></em></a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="/media/uploads/2024/07/22/image-20240722121752-1.png" /></h3>	3	Toplayacamz yumurta saysn artrmak iin 10-12 gn boyunca hergn uyarc ila enjeksiyonu yapacaksnz. Bu dnemde kan testleri ve ultrason muayeneleri ile tedaviye verdiiniz yant takip edeceiz ve ila dozunu ayarlayacaz.
13	tr	Yumurta Toplama	yumurta-toplama	<h3>Yumurta Toplama ve Sperm &Ouml;rneinin Alnmas:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Yumurtalarnz yaklak 30 dakika kadar s&uuml;ren ksa bir ilem ile toplanr </strong>ve bu srada size damardan hafif bir anestezi verilir, b&ouml;ylece herhangi bir ac hissetmezsiniz. Ayn g&uuml;n, einizden meni &ouml;rnei alnacaktr.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Yumurta toplamann zaman, tetikleyici inenin yapld saate baldr. </strong>&Ouml;rnein, tetikleyici ine(ler) pazartesi akam saat 10&#39;da uygulanrsa, yumurta toplama ilemi &ccedil;aramba sabah saat 10&#39;da ger&ccedil;ekletirilecektir. Yaplacak tetikleyici inelerin t&uuml;r&uuml; ve says, kiiselletirilmi tedavi plannza baldr.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Yumurta toplama ilemi i&ccedil;in hastaneye geldiinizde, </strong>ekibimiz size &nbsp;elik edecektir. Hemireniz intraven&ouml;z (IV) serum takmadan &ouml;nce rutin vital bulgularnz &ouml;l&ccedil;ecektir. Daha sonra yumurta toplama ileminin ayrntlarn g&ouml;zden ge&ccedil;irmek i&ccedil;in t&uuml;p bebek doktorunuzla g&ouml;r&uuml;eceksiniz.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Ayrca yumurta toplama ilemi i&ccedil;in kullanlacak anestezi hakknda bilgi verecek olan anestezi uzman ile de g&ouml;r&uuml;eceksiniz. </strong>lem i&ccedil;in hazr olduunuzda, hemireniz size cerrahi s&uuml;ite kadar elik edecek ve burada ekibiniz ilem masasna d&uuml;z bir ekilde uzanmanza yardmc olacaktr. Solunumunuza yardmc olmak &uuml;zere oksijen verilmesi i&ccedil;in y&uuml;z&uuml;n&uuml;ze bir maske yerletirilecek ve uyutulacaksnz. Uyutulduunuz s&uuml;re boyunca kendi kendinize nefes alacaksnz. &nbsp; Anestezi ilemi hissetmenizi veya hatrlamanz &ouml;nleyecek ve damar (IV) yolundan uygulanacaktr.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Sedasyon altnda uykuya daldktan sonra, </strong>doktorunuz ve tbbi bakm ekibiniz jinekolojik muayenede olduu gibi size pozisyon verecektir. lemden &ouml;nce doktorunuz enfeksiyon riskini ortadan kaldrmak i&ccedil;in vajinay &ouml;zel bir sol&uuml;syonla temizleyecektir. Ultrason probu, yumurtalklarn ve folik&uuml;llerinin yan sra mesane, barsaklar ve ana kan damarlarnn konumunu belirlemek i&ccedil;in vajinaya yerletirilecektir.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Daha sonra, </strong>ultrason probundaki bir kanaldan ince bir ine ge&ccedil;irilecektir. ne vajinadan ge&ccedil;irilip ultrason teknolojisi kullanlarak yumurtalklarnzdaki her bir folik&uuml;l&uuml;n i&ccedil;ine y&ouml;nlendirilecektir. Folik&uuml;llerin i&ccedil;indeki sv, emme yoluyla aspire edilecek (&ccedil;karlacak) ve yumurtann varln dorulamak i&ccedil;in embriyoloji uzman tarafndan mikroskop altnda incelenecektir.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>T&uuml;m folik&uuml;ller aspire edildikten sonra, doktorunuz anormal bir kanama olmadn dorulamak i&ccedil;in bir ultrason muayenesi yapacaktr. T&uuml;m s&uuml;re&ccedil; genellikle 20 dakika veya daha ksa bir s&uuml;re i&ccedil;inde tamamlanr.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Yumurta toplama ileminin ardndan </strong>anestezi sonras takip odasna transfer edileceksiniz; burada hemireniz bakm ve destek salamak &uuml;zere hazr bulunacaktr.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Tamamen uyandnzda, </strong>doktorunuz yumurta toplama ileminin sonu&ccedil;larn ve elde edilen yumurta saysn sizinle paylaacaktr. Toparlanma s&uuml;recinde hemireniz oksijen seviyenizi, kan basncnz, kalp at hznz ve ar seviyenizi yakndan izleyecektir..<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><img src="/media/uploads/2024/07/22/image-20240722121752-1.png" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<em>Sradaki Adm:</em> <em><u><a href="https://drsagiroglu.com/tr/adim-adim-tup-bebek?item=retrieval-collection"><span style="color:#e72254">5. F</span></a></u></em><a href="https://drsagiroglu.com/tr/adim-adim-tup-bebek?item=retrieval-collection"><em><u><span style="color:#e72254">ertilizasyon</span></u></em></a><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="/media/uploads/2024/07/22/image-20240722121752-1.png" /></h3>	4	Yumurtalarnz yaklak 30 dakika kadar sren ksa bir ilem ile toplanr ve bu srada size damardan hafif bir anestezi verilir, bylece herhangi bir ac hissetmezsiniz. Ayn gn